First, I get the data and discard the last 4 rows since UGS has missing data in these rows. Then, I simplify columns names for easier usage.

hw2_data <- read.csv("IE360_Spring22_HW2_data.csv")
f28 <- hw2_data[1:28,]
colnames(f28) <- c('Quarter','UGS','RNUV','NLPG','PU','PG','NUGV','NDGV','GNPA','GNPC','GNP')

Moreover, I need to prepare data, because some columns have spaces in their values. Also, I convert Quarter column to date.

f28$Quarter=as.Date(as.yearqtr(f28$Quarter, format = "%Y_Q%q"))
f28$UGS=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(f28$UGS),fixed=TRUE))
f28$RNUV=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(f28$RNUV),fixed=TRUE))
f28$NLPG=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(f28$NLPG),fixed=TRUE))
f28$NUGV=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(f28$NUGV),fixed=TRUE))
f28$GNPA=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(f28$GNPA),fixed=TRUE))
f28$GNPC=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(f28$GNPC),fixed=TRUE))
f28$GNP=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(f28$GNP),fixed=TRUE))

I also define Trend and Quart for f28 data for further usage in models.

f28$Trend=seq(0,27,by=1)
f28$Quart=seq(1,4,by=1)

Lets define lag 1 and lag 4 as well.

f28$lag1 <- NA
f28$lag4 <- NA
f28$lag1 <- dplyr::lag(f28$UGS, 1L)
f28$lag4 <- dplyr::lag(f28$UGS, 4L)

I plot the data

plot(f28$Quarter,f28$UGS,type="l", xlab="quarters", ylab="UGS",main="UGS over years")

From plot above, it is seen that this time series has non-stationary mean and stationary variance.

acf(f28$UGS)

lag 1 has a significant value which indicates the trend, since each quarter is affected by the prior quarter. Also, lag 4 has a significant value which indicates seasonality.

UGS=f28$UGS
UGSts <- ts(UGS, freq=4, start=c(2000,1))
UGSdec<-decompose(UGSts,type="additive")
plot(UGSdec)

I decomposed data to have a better look.

So, best model so far is model 9, lets use it and forecast.

hw2_data <- read.csv("IE360_Spring22_HW2_data.csv")
colnames(hw2_data) <- c('Quarter','UGS','RNUV','NLPG','PU','PG','NUGV','NDGV','GNPA','GNPC','GNP')
hw2_data$Quarter=as.Date(as.yearqtr(hw2_data$Quarter, format = "%Y_Q%q"))
hw2_data$UGS=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(hw2_data$UGS),fixed=TRUE))
hw2_data$RNUV=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(hw2_data$RNUV),fixed=TRUE))
hw2_data$NLPG=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(hw2_data$NLPG),fixed=TRUE))
hw2_data$NUGV=as.numeric(gsub(" ","",as.character(hw2_data$NUGV),fixed=TRUE))

hw2_data$Trend=seq(0,31,by=1)
